hoarse /hɔːs/

(hoarser,hoarsest) 

1. ADJ If your voice is hoarse or if you are hoarse , your voice sounds rough and unclear, for example because your throat is sore. 嘶哑的 

例： 'So what do you think?' she said in a hoarse whisper. “那么你怎么认为？”她用嘶哑的嗓音悄声说道。 

2. hoarsely ADV 嘶哑地 

例： 'Thank you,' Maria said hoarsely. “谢谢，”玛丽亚嗓音嘶哑地说道。

